After three marathon sessions of negotiations, the unions of the road sector and the TLF (Transport and Logistics of France), the only employers' organization that remained until the end, reached an agreement on Friday afternoon that ends the strike slogan and the threat that falls on Christmas supplies.
During the signing session on Friday night, Secretary of State for Transport Dominique Bussereau was "pleased" by the agreement, after several negotiation sessions began on Wednesday morning.
