The conflict "would have been very damaging to businesses" and "it was feared that it would disrupt the holidays," Bussereau said.
The text provides for an increase of 4% for the lowest wages (in local and regional road transport), and 2.9% for the highest (international transport).
The hourly rate rises from 8.72 euros to 9.06 for low wages.
