It will be done "as soon as possible," Bussereau said.
Opposition from employers' organizations could only delay the process.
The FNTR denounced that it was a "naïve business", since the 100 million euros "had already been promised to the sector to offset part of the CO2 tax".
The Secretary of State for Transport forced us to negotiate in an emergency situation, not as a conclusion to an analysis discussed by the parties, but not to antagonize those who want to eat turkey at the next Christmas Eve dinner, lamented Unostra.
For OTRE, the agreement puts at risk "the stability of many SMEs in the sector during the next 12 months."
