Turkey cannot resolve this issue (Kurdish, NDLR) by dissolving a party, he told reporters.
The government, formed by a party from the Islamist movement, also regrets the decision.
As a matter of principle, we are opposed to the closure of matches.
That doesn't solve anything, Energy Minister Taner Yildiz said.
