But also the accesses for the fire brigade, public transport routes, pedestrian areas and sections with slopes, such as Atzelbergstraße.
The FES service starts around three in the morning
They should be covered approximately 1,040 kilometers, as needed, in a maximum of three hours with wet salt, which adheres better.
That is why the FES begins around three in the morning, "with it the roads are free until the traffic of the peak hours begins".
The difficult thing is when it starts to snow around 7:30 am.
"Then we have a problem," says the director of road maintenance in winter, "because then no one is ready to clear space for vehicles with salt."
Immediately afterwards, when it is no longer snowing, it is the turn of the secondary and private roads, to which the Rat-Beil-Straße also belongs.
The last priority is the side and secondary streets.
That's where the discomfort is generated, Brauburger knows well.
Around five o'clock in the morning the FES infantry is launched, mainly dangerous points and cruisers are cleared.
FES would generally not be able to take care of all bike lanes.
