Workshop budget in four steps
With the Auda-Workshop tool, the company Audatex guarantees that the user obtains a quote in just four steps: identify the vehicle, search for the spare part, create a budget and generate a budget.
Ease of use is an essential condition for these systems, especially to convince older professionals, who to a greater or lesser extent tend to be more reluctant to use new management techniques.
The database includes 1,034 vehicles, which are 666 passenger cars, 109 SUVs, 137 motorcycles, 78 vans and 44 trucks.
Naturally, to use it you need a computer with an internet connection.
Once the model to be repaired has been identified by its chassis number, a real graphic image of the model in question appears and then the necessary spare part is selected.
The user can include variables such as the price of labor, surcharges or discounts, and then can print the budget to deliver to the client.
